backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet address — read

An address is the link between a logical location (`emp/7/name`) and a physical one (the bits in
the record). This drives the first slice — `addressRead` — over an in-memory image: parsing,
resolution, the per-type answers, and the two facts that make the link observable rather than
assumed (`fromRowid`, `physicalBytes`).

Note what this case can and cannot prove. The image here is written by scljet and read by scljet,
so it is a **self-consistent oracle**: it pins the shape of the answers, but it cannot see a
file-format divergence. The IPK link is only truly proven by a differential that crosses two
engines through a FILE — that lives in the JVM lane (`ScljetAddressTest`), where a real SQLite
writer is available. Spec: `specs/scljet-address.md`.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlNull, SqlInteger, SqlText, SqlReal, SqlBlob, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[SqliteAddress, AddressedValue, parseAddress, renderAddress, addressRead](std/scljet/address.ssc)

```scalascript
def showValue(v: SqliteValue): String = v match
  case SqlNull => "NULL"
  case SqlInteger(x) => x.toString
  case SqlReal(x) => x.toString
  case SqlText(x) => x
  case _ => "?"

def readAt(image: ByteSlice, text: String): Unit =
  parseAddress(text) match
    case Left(message) => println(text + " => ERR " + message)
    case Right(addr) => addressRead(image, addr) match
      case Left(message) => println(renderAddress(addr) + " => ERR " + message)
      case Right(av) =>
        println(renderAddress(addr) + " => " + av.typeName + " " + showValue(av.value) +
          " | physical=" + av.physicalBytes.toString + "B" +
          " fromRowid=" + av.fromRowid.toString +
          " stable=" + av.stable.toString)

// A table WITH an INTEGER PRIMARY KEY: the addresses into it are stable, and `id` is an alias
// for the rowid.
buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, bonus REAL)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlReal(1.5)),
       List(SqlInteger(7L), SqlText("bob"), SqlReal(2.5)),
       List(SqlInteger(9L), SqlText("cat"), SqlNull))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build failed: " + error.message)
  case Right(image) =>
    println("-- an IPK table: addresses are stable --")
    readAt(image, "emp/7/name")
    readAt(image, "emp/7/id")
    readAt(image, "emp/7/bonus")
    readAt(image, "emp/1/name")
    readAt(image, "emp/9/bonus")

    println("-- addresses that do not resolve are errors, not guesses --")
    readAt(image, "emp/42/name")
    readAt(image, "emp/7/nope")
    readAt(image, "nosuch/1/x")

    println("-- a malformed address is an explicit error --")
    readAt(image, "emp/7")
    readAt(image, "emp/x/name")
    readAt(image, "emp//name")
    println(renderAddress(SqliteAddress("emp", 7L, "name")))

// A table WITHOUT an INTEGER PRIMARY KEY: the same address form is positional — a VACUUM by any
// writer may renumber the rowids and quietly point it at a different row. We say so.
buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "log", "CREATE TABLE log(a INTEGER, b TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(10L), SqlText("x")),
       List(SqlInteger(20L), SqlText("y")))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build failed: " + error.message)
  case Right(image) =>
    println("-- no IPK: same address form, but NOT stable --")
    readAt(image, "log/1/a")
    readAt(image, "log/2/b")
```
